                    --_--_--_--_--_--_--_--_--_--_--_--
                          Bi-directional Graph
                    --_--_--_--_--_--_--_--_--_--_--_--

Use:
  'make' to compile.
  'make clean' to remove the objects.
  './graph' to execute.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Commands:
  'i' to insert a new node.
  'd' to delete a node.
  'p' to print the graph.
  'g' to use the greedy algorithm.
  'f' to free the graph.
  'e' to exit.

  OBS: All commands without ''.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Inserting a new node:
  Enter the name of the node (use char type).
  Example: 'A'.

  After, enter the neighbors of the node (use char type), without space.
  Example: 'B''D'.
          Not 'A' 'B' 'D'.

  To finish the insertion, enter the cost of the neighbors (use integer type).
  Example: 10
           20
            5

  If the node does not any neighbors, press 'Enter' without neighbor.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Deleting a node:
  Enter the name of the node (use char type).
  Example: 'A'.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Using the greedy algorithm:
  Enter the name of the node to start (use char type).
  Example: 'A'.
